com.kuka.roboticsAPI.motionModel

Interface ISunriseMotionExtended

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAction, com.kuka.motion.IMotion, ISunriseMotion
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbsoluteSplineMotionCP, AbstractSunriseMotion, CartesianPTP, CIRC, LIN, MotionBatch, PositionHold, PTP, PTPHome, RelativeCIRC, RelativeLIN, RelativeSPL, RelativeSplineMotionCP, RobotMotion, SPL, Spline, SplineJP, SplineMotion, SplineMotionCP, SplineMotionJP

    public interface ISunriseMotionExtended
extends ISunriseMotion
    Represents a generic Sunrise motion, with the additional features of setting a motion overlay and adding motion conditions.
    This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

    • Method Detail

      • breakWhen

        ISunriseMotionExtended breakWhen(com.kuka.condition.ICondition condition)
        Adds a condition to this motion.

        The execution of the motion will be finished if the specified condition is evaluated to true. If the next motion is ready to be executed at that moment, it will start immediately.

        Parameters:
        condition - The condition. null is not allowed.
        Returns:
        This motion.

      • triggerWhen

        ISunriseMotionExtended triggerWhen(com.kuka.condition.ICondition condition,
                                   ITriggerAction action)
        Adds a trigger to this motion. For user defined actions, please use callbackWhen(ICondition, ICallbackAction).

        The specified action will be executed whenever the specified condition is evaluated to true. If the execution of the action is still in progress, when the next trigger occurs, the action is not executed again. The action is only executed when the trigger occurs while no action execution is in progress. Action callback has a method to determine the number of missed triggers.

        Parameters:
        condition - The condition. null is not allowed.
        action - The action to execute when the condition is evaluated to true.
        Returns:
        This motion.
        See Also:
        ICallbackAction, StartRecordingAction, StopRecordingAction

      • callbackWhen

        ISunriseMotionExtended callbackWhen(com.kuka.condition.ICondition condition,
                                    ICallbackAction action)
        Adds a user-defined callback action to this motion. Equivalent to triggerWhen(ICondition, ITriggerAction) but accepts an ICallbackAction parameter.
        Parameters:
        condition - The condition. null is not allowed.
        action - The action to execute when the condition is evaluated to true.
        Returns:
        This motion.
